               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311020-67-person563">
                  THOMAS 
                  KING
               <interp inst="t18311020-67-person563" type="surname" value="KING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311020-67-person563" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311020-67-person563" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , I am a Policeman. On the 30th of September, about seven o'clock in the evening, I saw the prisoners with another boy at Pentonville, loitering about a shoemaker's shop; I watched them for half an hour, and saw Hitchcock crawl into Offord's shop, on his hands and knees, and take this bacon out: Maginn had an apron on - Hitchcock gave it to him, and he put it into his apron; he was standing outside, about two shops off, and a third boy stood opposite; I crossed, and seized the prisoners.</p>
               <p>RICHARD OFFORD. I keep a chandler's-shop at Pentonville; King brought the prisoners in - he had the bacon in his hand: I am sure it was mine - nobody was in the shop at the time.</p>
               <p>Hitchcock's Defence. A boy gave it to me - I gave it to Maginn.</p>
               <p>Maginn's Defence. I saw the other boy take the bacon out of the shop, and give it to Hitchcock.</p>
               <p>HITCHCOCK - <rs id="t18311020-67-verdict348" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311020-67-verdict348" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 9.</p>
               <p>MAGINN - <rs id="t18311020-67-verdict349" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311020-67-verdict349" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 16.</p>
